article.headline: Drake 82, Evansville 79
article.story: DES MOINES, Iowa (AP) -- Nick Grant had a career-high 25 points and Drake held off a late rally to beat Evansville 82-79 Wednesday night. Grant was 9-of-15 from the floor and had two crucial layups as the Bulldogs avenged an earlier loss to the Purple Aces and assured themselves their first winning season in 20 years. Drake (16-13, 6-11 Missouri Valley Conference) was cruising in the second half and built a 61-44 lead with 12:28 left. But Evansville (14-15, 6-11 MVC) went on a 16-1 run to cut the lead to 62-60 with 7:08 to play. Jason Holslinger, who finished with a career high 29 points, hit four 3-pointers during the run. Kyle Aslinger's two free throws cut the lead to 76-74 with 51 seconds left. After a Drake timeout, Klayton Korver drained a 3 from the right corner to give the Bulldogs a 79-74 cushion with 34 seconds left. Ajay Calvin chipped in 16 and Al Stewart and Josh Young each had 10 for the Bulldogs. Matt Webster finished with 16 for the Purple Aces. Evansville hit 13 of its 30 3-point attempts.
